text.__SUMMARY__: Cyperus oxycarpus is a sedge of the family Cyperaceae that is native to Australia.The rhizomatous perennial sedge typically grows to a height of 0.3 to 0.9 metres (1.0 to 3.0 ft) and has a tufted habit. It blooms between March and April and produces brown flowers.In Western Australia it is found around wet areas in the Kimberley region where it grows in clay soils.
